    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a901bcb_fec2c1aa",
        "filename": "libminijail.c",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 209,
      "author": {
        "id": 1076138
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-01-08T19:26:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If j-\u003eflags.suppl_gids \u003d 1, then minijail_enter() will do a call to setgroups(j-\u003esuppl_gid_list), which is unneeded since the list is empty. We can avoid that by making this call not actually set the flag, since the result of not calling setgroups in minijail_enter() and calling it with an empty list is equivalent.",
      "parentUuid": "4a8b57a3_e0f21cc2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 206,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 209,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "84e67ddc37724b953c02c10f5a8154c3b226b0c0",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4a8b57a3_4065901b",
        "filename": "libminijail.c",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 209,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003966
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-01-08T20:05:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m confused how it\u0027s equivalent. Imagine a process starts with UID\u003d0 GID\u003d0 supplemental_GID\u003d1,2. \n\nI then make the following sequence of calls with the intention of clearing my supplemental GIDs while retaining UID/GID\u003d0.\n\n  minijail_set_supplementary_gids(j, 0, NULL)\n  minijail_enter(j);\n\nIt looks like this will be a no-op then? setgroups() is only called if j-\u003eflags.suppl_gids is set (line 1052), or if (j-\u003euid || j-\u003egid) (line 1060), neither of which is true in the case above.\n\n(on an aside, I don\u0027t understand why UID\u003d0 is special cased on line 1060, since it\u0027s quite possible that UID\u003d0 is running without DAC_OVERRIDE. This is done, for example, in some Android daemons controlled by SELinux.)",
      "parentUuid": "6a901bcb_fec2c1aa",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 206,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 209,
        "endChar": 2
      },
